		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Megaman 7 was very cool and I feel privileged to own a copy, but it doesn't hold a candle to Megaman X2, released in the same year. 
<br />
<br />As ironic as it sounds, I'd say Megaman 7 is probably a good 7/10. It definetely felt more fresh than sleeper Megaman 6, it gave is Bass, Shademan and his theme is awesome, and it's nice to see the game still carries a premium all these years later. Still, that damn wily battle was among the most frustrating boss battles of any Megaman game EVER.

		

